Review: Sadly the only thing super here was the budget. Over 225,000,000. And that's about it. A few pretty shots here and there and a nice cast couldn't save this movie.

January 2nd, cup of black coffee, and it looks like I've found a film to rewatch during the holiday season. The right amount of feels-- both melancholic and warm. The performances are nothing short of stellar and the soundtrack just adds a beautiful touch.
A great way to start the new year! The plot here is very simple, but Eddie Murphy elevates things with an excellent performance.
This is a good biopic. I'm surprised at how captivated I was-- at times literally on the edge of my seat. Time to play some Forza.

Movie: Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy

Review: This movie is at least 90% puns.
This movie teeters from sexual to overly cartoony, and not in a good way.
Wasn't a fan of the music, but the story overall was sweet and captivating. Also, it's always great to hear Norm Macdonald's voice!

Movie: Star Wars: Episode III – Revenge of the Sith

Review: This movie has a lot of heart and some really solid jokes here and there. Bill Burr and Adam Sandler, in particular, were great. But then the movie would stubbornly go into musical mode... a lot. Too much. I like a good musical, but not this.
